parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sliding doors can cause inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents, especially in emergency situations where occupants need to exit the vehicle quickly.
symptoms: The sliding doors do not open or close properly
the doors stick or jam
the doors make loud clicking or popping noises
the doors do not respond to the door handles
the doors open or close intermittently
the doors do not lock properly
and the doors rattle while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lift gate can cause inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents, especially when the gate suddenly closes or falls, causing injury or damage.
symptoms: The lift gate does not open or close properly
the gate falls or closes suddenly
the gate does not respond to the handle
the gate makes loud noises
and the gas struts fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Spare Tire Carrier Assembly Cable Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the spare tire carrier assembly cable can cause the spare tire to become dislodged, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The spare tire carrier assembly cable is corroded
the spare tire is not securely attached
and the spare tire may become dislodged while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sliding door latch can cause the door to stick or not open, trapping occupants inside, which can lead to accidents or injuries in emergency situations.
symptoms: The sliding door will not open or close
the door latch button gets stuck
the door will not latch
the door can only be opened from the outside
the door will not open manually from the inside
the door requires brute strength to open.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power locks can cause the doors to lock or unlock unpredictably, which can lead to safety issues, such as children being trapped inside or theft.
symptoms: The power locks function intermittently
the doors lock or unlock unpredictably
the doors will not lock or unlock.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood latch can cause the hood to blow open while driving, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The hood blows open while driving
the hood latch fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without the driver's input
often when the brake pedal is pressed or when the vehicle is on a hill.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission and gear shift problems can cause the vehicle to become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The gear shift linkage breaks
the vehicle is stuck in reverse
the transmission hesitates or shifts hard
the vehicle will not shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear axle and differential problems can cause vibration, noise, and loss of control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: Loud/squeaking/grinding noise in the rear axle
vibration at various speeds
harmonic distortion on the rear axle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and hydraulic system failure can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overdrive feature design can cause the vehicle to roll freely without engine braking, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle defaults to overdrive mode
which disables engine braking
requiring the driver to push a button to engage engine braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floorboard
the vehicle shakes uncontrollably
the vehicle creeps forward while stopped
loud squeaking or grinding noises are heard when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle shakes uncontrollably
loud squeaking or grinding noises are heard when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly
the brake pedal does not respond when applied
the vehicle creeps forward while stopped.
